CHANGELIST
----------
= Version 2.1.5 =
* October 10, 2011
* The Farsi localization wasn't being made available, and had to be indicated in the plist file.

= Version 2.1.4 =
* August 30, 2011
* The GMT bug was not a bug. However, there was an issue with the welcome/congratulations not erasing properly. That is fixed.

= Version 2.1.3 =
* August 30, 2011
* Fixed a bug in which the local time was not being properly offset from GMT.

= Version 2.1.2 =
* August 27, 2011
* Improved Farsi support.

= Version 2.1.1 =
* August 9, 2011
* Fixed a bug, where the "shadow" wasn't being displayed.
* Farsi (Persian) localization.
* Changed the splash screen, so that we won't have a mismatch with localized versions.

= Version 2.1 =
* August 2, 2011
* Made the application extremely localizable.
* Added a "Cancel" button to the date picker.
* Added a "Today" button to the date picker.
* The date picker now appears in a popover for iPads, and a modal window for iPhones and iPods.
* Added a choice to set or remove the date limits on the date picker (new setting).
* Made some of the internal code more efficient and robust.
* Added "gravity scrolling" to the tag results (new setting).

= Version 2.0 =
* July 25, 2011
* Massive overhaul. The app now has three screens: Calculate, Settings and Info.
* Many cosmetic enhancements.
* Now can save the date, clear results and select options.
* Resubmitted to App Store, so 2.0 should now be the first version available.

= Version 1.0.1 =
* July 23, 2011
* Fixed a number of layout bugs that prevented the app from being rotated.
* Fixed a small memory leak.
* Resubmitted to App Store, so 1.0.1 should be the first version available.

= Version 1.0 =
* July 22, 2011
* Initial check-in of GitHub project
* First submission to Apple App Store
